<FILEID>AP-NR-05-31-89 0247EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r w PM-WashingtonBriefs     05-31 0543</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Washington Briefs,550</SECOND>
<HEAD>Legislators Targeted in Abortion Ads</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The latest advertising campaign in the fight
over abortion rights is being sponsored by the National Abortion
Rights Action League and is aimed at newspaper readers in
congressional districts.
   ``Many of the constituents in districts around the country do
not know what their congresspeople say and do regarding a woman's
right to choose,'' NARAL executive director Kate Michelman said
Tuesday.
   The league's first target is freshman Rep. Craig James, a
Florida Republican who last year narrowly defeated veteran Rep.
Bill Chappell.
   Michelman said her group has gathered a store of ``tremendously
outrageous statements about reproductive rights and women in
general'' from other legislators and is developing a list of
targets, of which James is the first.
</TEXT>
