<HEAD>Coke Says Promotion Could Endanger Kids</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Coca-Cola foods is recalling a promotional
item because small children could choke on a plastic locking device
that holds the bands in place, says the Consumer Product Safety
Commission.
   The item, ``Cool Cuffs,'' is a version of a colored wrist band
used in hospitals, amusement parks and summer playgrounds. It was
distributed as a promotional item for Hi-C fruit drinks from
February through April.
   The CPSC said Tuesday that 2 million were distributed with
nine-packs of the drink and more through a mail-in offer.
