<FIRST>r a PM-DyingBoy     05-31 0242</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Dying Boy,0249</SECOND>
<HEAD>Father Takes Child Being Treated for Leukemia From Hospital</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A father distraught over his 5-year-old son's
suffering from leukemia took the child from a hospital where he was
undergoing court-ordered treatment, police said today.
   David Pagan, 36, took his son, Darian, from Memorial
Sloan-Kettering Hospital sometime Sunday.
   ``We have no reason to believe the child is in any danger from
his father,'' said Sgt. Ed Burns, who added that the father's
action violated a court order.
   Sgt. Raymond O'Donnell said the father ``had indicated that he
didn't want the boy to suffer and that he wanted him to enjoy
life.''
   Pagan's brother-in-law told the Daily News that Darian had been
complaining of pain and that his father wanted to take the boy to
Walt Disney World in Florida.
   But police said they think Pagan may have taken Darian to a
cancer-treatment center in Arlington, Texas.
   Darian was hospitalized Friday under a court order requested by
the city's Child Welfare Administration because officials said the
boy was not getting the treatment he needed.
   The parents are Jehovah's Witnesses, who do not approve of blood
transfusions. But the News quoted an unidentified relative as
saying religion had nothing to do with the parents' objections to
treatment.
   The mother, Migdalia, 35, noticed Darian was missing from the
hospital Sunday evening and alerted staff. Police said the father
had been with his son at the hospital all day.
</TEXT>
