<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--TankAccident     05-31 0079</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Tank Accident,0080</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Soldiers Killed, Two Hurt in Tank Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two Italian soldiers were killed and two were
injured Wednesday when their tank fell off a cliff after a military
exercise, according to media reports.
   The M-13 tank was returning to base in Pietralata, a
northeastern suburb of the capital, after a morning of military
exercises when it fell off a 164-foot cliff, the reports said.
   The cause of the accident was under investigation.
</TEXT>
