<HEAD>Motorists May Go With The Flow On Proposed Freeway</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Transportation officials are considering
opening up a road that would give new meaning to the term car pool.
   The concrete-lined Los Angeles River, dry 300 days a year, would
make a perfect alternate freeway route and speed the flow of
traffic, transportation planners said.
