   Sam Michael Fox was born Tuesday afternoon, publicist Nancy
Ryder said. The exact time, location and birth weight weren't
disclosed.
   ``They are doing fine,'' Ms. Ryder said.
   Fox, 27, and Miss Pollan, 28, were married at an inn in
Arlington, Vt., in July 1988 with tight security guarding their
privacy from helicopter-borne photographers and reporters.
   Miss Pollan played the college-age artist girlfriend to Fox's
insufferably conservative Alex Keaton on ``Family Ties,'' for which
he won two Emmys. The high-rated TV series called it quits this
month after a seven-year run on NBC, but continues in reruns.
   Fox and Miss Pollan also starred in the film ``Bright Lights,
Big City.'' Fox rocketed to fame when he starred in the 1985 movie
``Back to the Future.'' He co-stars with Sean Penn in the upcoming
film ``Casualties of War.''
   Fox has been pestered by a woman accused of sending more than
5,000 letters threatening him, his wife and child with death.
   Tina Marie Ledbetter, 26, has been charged with five counts of
making terrorist threats and faces Superior Court arraignment
Monday in Los Angeles. She was being held without bail.
