<DATELINE>NORWALK, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman who claimed to be the wife of NBC
talk show host David Letterman and repeatedly broke into his house
has pleaded guilty to trepassing charges and agreed to stay away
from him.
   As part of a plea bargain arrangement, a Norwalk judge Tuesday
sentenced Margaret Ray, 37, to a one-year suspended sentence and
three years' probation.
   The judge ordered Ray released from a state mental hospital,
where she had been confined since April, after being found
incompetent to stand trial.
   As a condition of probation, Ray must stay away from Letterman
and continue to undergo psychiatric treatment, Assistant State's
Attorney Robert G. Hall Jr. said. He said he believes Ray is
returning home to Crawford, Colo.
   Ray was arrested in June 1988 when she tried to pass herself off
as Letterman's wife after she was stopped while driving his
Porsche. Police said they later discovered someone had broken into
Letterman's home and had been living there for several days while
