<HEAD>Retired Motorcycle Policeman Escorting Movie Crew Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A retired policeman escorting a camera truck
filming the movie ``Dead Men Don't Die'' was knocked off his
motorcycle by a car that dragged him 200 feet to his death,
authorities said Wednesday.
   Film company members, watching helplessly as the car rounded a
corner and struck the officer, rushed to the auto after the driver
fled and lifted it off the motorcyclist.
   ``The right front wheel came to rest on top of the officer. They
lifted the car up but he died,'' police Detective John Gibson said.
   Alan DeLapp, 60, retired from the Los Angeles Police Department
