<HEAD>Coke Says `Cool Cuffs' Could Endanger Tykes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Coca-Cola foods is recalling a promotional
item _ brightly colored wrist bands _ on grounds that small
children could choke on a plastic locking device that holds the
bands in place, the Consumer Product Safety Commission said.
   The item, called ``Cool Cuffs,'' is a version of a wrist band
used in hospitals, amusement parks and summer playgrounds. It was
distributed as a promotional item for Hi-C fruit drinks from
February through April.
   The CPSC said Tuesday that 2 million were distributed with
nine-packs of the drink and more through a mail-in offer.
   The agency advised parents to take the item away from children
under three and either discard them or return them to Hi-C for
replacement with another premium.
