<SECOND>PM-Wall Street Noon,0417</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices were mixed in moderate trading
today, amid a weakening dollar and a new economic report indicating
U.S. industry is advancing at a healthy clip.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was down 1.29 points to
2,474.26 at noon EDT. The blue-chip indicator was 1.84 points lower
an hour earlier.
   Advancing and declining issues were even on the New York Stock
Exchange, with 602 issues up, 602 down and 601 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board totaled 73.66 million shares.
   After slight gains early in the day, stock prices weakened,
taking a cue from softening bond prices as the U.S. dollar headed
toward the day's lows, although it remained firm against the
Japanese yen and West German mark.
   ``A lower dollar hurts bonds which hurts equities,'' said Dennis
Jarrett, technical analyst with Kidder, Peabody &amp; Co.
   Also pressuring stocks was a government report that U.S. factory
orders rose 2.7 percent in April.
   It was the best showing in four months, and led to new
speculation that the Federal Reserve might not lower interest rates
any time soon as earlier suggested.
   Expectations had grown over the last several days that the Fed
might lower interest rates to stem the rising dollar. But analysts
said after today's factory orders report that such a move by the
Fed is unlikely given its concerns about inflation.
   Earlier today, stock prices rose after the Commerce Department
reported that its chief economic forecasting gauge, the Index of
Leading Economic Indicators, shot up 0.8 percent in April after
declining during the previous two months.
   Analysts said April's upturn, which had been widely anticipated,
was consistent with the view that while the economy is slowing,
there still is enough strength left to power the record peacetime
expansion through its seventh year. Also, the number was not strong
enough to engender new fears about inflation, analysts said.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks was
up 0.08 to 178.19.
   At the American Stock Exchange, the market value index had
gained 0.28 to 354.69.
   Among blue-chip stocks, IBM was up { to 108}, Warner
Communications was up 1 to 51~ and USX Corp. had advanced [ to 34}.
   Airline stocks were broadly lower with Northwest Airlines down ~
to 106], Pan Am off [ to 4| and Delta Airlines down } to 69\.
