<FILEID>AP-NR-05-31-89 2328EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-AffiliatedPublications     05-31 0189</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Affiliated Publications,0196</SECOND>
<HEAD>Parent Of Boston Globe Restructures To Separate Holdings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Affiliated Publications Inc., parent company of
Globe Newspaper Co. and Billboard Publications Inc., announced
Wednesday a restructuring that would separate those companies from
ownership interests in McCaw Cellular Communications Inc., a
cellular-phone company.
   In February, API Print Corp. was created to hold Affiliated's
two main subsidiaries: Globe Newspaper, publisher of The Boston
Globe, and Billboard Publications, Affiliated said.
   After a vote at Wednesday's shareholders meeting, one share of
Class A common stock and one share of Class B common stock of API
Print were issued for each outstanding share of company stock,
Affiliated Vice President William B. Huff said.
   Affiliated then merged its equity interest in McCaw Cellular. As
a result, McCaw Cellular will distribute 58,522,638 shares of its
stock on a basis of approximately 0.84 shares of McCaw stock for
every share of Affiliated stock held on May 31.
   After Wednesday's transactions, API Print changed its name to
Affiliated Publications, the company said.
   Affiliated shareholders now own stock in two different
companies: the newly constituted Affiliated Publications Inc. and
McCaw Cellular Communications Inc.
</TEXT>
